docs.snippet: Alberto Gainza Paz, the editor and publisher of La Prensa of Buenos Aires, considered one of the world's leading newspapers, died early yesterday morning in his home in the Argentine capital. He was 78 years old and had had cancer for some time.
docs.lead_paragraph: Alberto Gainza Paz, the editor and publisher of La Prensa of Buenos Aires, considered one of the world's leading newspapers, died early yesterday morning in his home in the Argentine capital. He was 78 years old and had had cancer for some time.

headline.main: Alberto Gainza Paz, 78, Is Dead; Editor Ran Argentina's La Prensa
